---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Distribution — AgentSON" description="Distribute AgentSON via Docker Hub, LXD Hub, PyPI, npm.">
  <section class="section hero" style="padding-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Distribution</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">AgentSON is distributed through every channel. Pick your runtime.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue);">
          <h3 class="text-blue">Docker Hub</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--text-dim);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">OCI Artifacts for agent sessions.</p>
          <pre style="margin:0;">docker pull agentson/cli
docker run agentson/cli export opencode

docker pull agentson/session:bug-fix-42
# .agentson file + provenance SBOM</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--green);">
          <h3 class="text-green">LXD Hub</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--text-dim);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">System containers for agent daemons.</p>
          <pre style="margin:0;">lxc image copy agentson/server:1.0

lxc launch agentson/server
# Persistent agent runtime
# with built-in provenance</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--orange);">
          <h3 class="text-orange">PyPI</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--text-dim);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">Python CLI and library.</p>
          <pre style="margin:0;">pip install agentson

agentson export opencode --all
agentson validate session.agentson
agentson render session.agentson</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--purple);">
          <h3 class="text-purple">npm</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--text-dim);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">JavaScript/TypeScript library (planned).</p>
          <pre style="margin:0;">npm install @agentson/cli

agentson stream start
# JSONL blackboard for
# real-time collaboration</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="background:var(--bg-card);border-top:1px solid var(--border);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:var(--max-prose);margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="section-title">Cross-Registry Compatibility</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">AgentSON sessions are portable across registries.</p>
      
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--space-md);">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Docker Hub 2.0 &rarr; LXD Hub</h3>
          <p>Pull an AgentSON session from Docker Hub as an OCI artifact. Re-publish as an LXD image for system-level agent runtime. No conversion needed — the .agentson file is the same.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>OCI Artifact Compatibility</h3>
          <p>Docker Hub 2.0 supports OCI Artifacts. AgentSON sessions are packaged as OCI layers with model-SBOM-style provenance metadata. LXD Hub pulls the same OCI layers and runs them as system containers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:var(--max-prose);text-align:center;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 class="section-title">AgentSON + Docker Agent = Full Stack</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Docker runs it. AgentSON records it.</p>
      <div class="card" style="text-align:left;">
        <pre style="margin:0;"># Define an agent
docker agent run andie/bug-fixer

# AgentSON captures everything:
#   action, thought, observation, 
#   tool-call, system-event, ...

# Distribute the session
docker push agentson/session:bug-fix-42

# Replay on any machine
docker run agentson/cli replay \
  agentson/session:bug-fix-42</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
